This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as hypernymy detection. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses recurrent neural networks and other machine learning techniques. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with semantic relationships between words. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with analyzing relationships between words in a network.
